    Download (PPT) 

Figure thumbnail gr6
FIGURE 6 The allosteric model for BK channel activation fits experimental data from three different BK channel mutants. The experimental GV and FV data for pWT ( A ), RCK1 mutant D362A/D367A ( B ), and RCK2 mutant D894N/D895N/D896N/D897N/D898N ( D894–898N , C ) were fitted simultaneously together with the data points describing the Ca 2+ dependence of the G V half ( D ). The continuous lines are the predictions of the BK allosteric model presented in Fig. 5 (experimental data are as in FIGURE 2 , FIGURE 3 , and supplemental Fig. S1C ). The fitted parameters are listed in Table 1 .

